Package ca.camosun.ics124.lab4

Interface List<E>

Type Parameters:
E - stored element type
public interface List<E>
A linear indexed collection. List element positions are indexed starting from 0. Negative positions may also be used, in which case the value will be interpreted as an offset from the end of the list. For example, the final element in any non-empty list may be accessed at the index -1.
Author:
Maxwell Terpstra

    • add

      void add(E element, int index) throws IndexOutOfBoundsException
      Insert an element at the given index. This element will be accessible at the index provided immediately after insertion. Note that this means that positive indexes will insert the element before an element already stored at that index whereas negative indexes will insert the element after.
      Parameters:
      element - element to be added
      index - position at which the new element will be inserted
      Throws:
      IndexOutOfBoundsException - if index ∉ [-size()-1, size()]

    • indexOf

      int indexOf(E element) throws NoSuchElementException

      element - the element to search for
      Returns:
      positive position index
      Throws:
      NoSuchElementException - if no stored value in this collection is equal to the given element
